er Satan or anything about his misdeeds. Could it be that they are too much on his mind for him to mention them? Possibly, yet Job mentions everything else, and does much more than mention. He dwells heavily on the cause of his misfortune, which is none of those mentioned in the prologue. The cause is not divine, satanic nor physical, but merely human.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / Old Testament.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503622999423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503622999/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles